                        <interp inst="t18770305-266-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>—<hi rend="italic">He was further charged with a previous conviction of a like offence.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770305-name-47" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-47" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-47" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-47" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BOLTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I was present here on 3rd May, 1875, when the prisoner was convicted and sentenced to
eighteen months' imprisonment for uttering counterfeit coin.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770305-name-48" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-48" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
